ğŸŒ Environment Variables (.env)

If not using IAM role, create:

nano .env


Add:

AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your_key
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your_secret
AWS_DEFAULT_REGION=ap-south-1


Load using:

from dotenv import load_dotenv
load_dotenv()


âš ï¸ Never push .env to GitHub. Add to .gitignore.

â— Errors You Faced & Fix
1ï¸âƒ£ CloudWatch Error

Cause:

No IAM role

Wrong region

No permissions

Fix:

Attach correct IAM role

Check region:

echo $AWS_DEFAULT_REGION


Test:

aws sts get-caller-identity


If this fails â†’ IAM issue.

2ï¸âƒ£ S3 Error

Cause:

No S3 permissions

Wrong bucket

AWS not configured

Test:

aws s3 ls


If AccessDenied â†’ IAM policy missing.

3ï¸âƒ£ Access Denied in Browser

Cause:

Port 5000 not open

Fix:

Edit EC2 Security Group

Allow inbound TCP 5000

4ï¸âƒ£ Public IP Changes

Use Elastic IP to make permanent.

